{
  "doc_id": "FC-LS",
  "source_pdf": "/Users/zwy/毕设/V7/data/raw/FC-LS.pdf",
  "page": 189,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0002",
      "text": " 170",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0003",
      "text": "The Clock synchronization capable bit (word 1, bit 19) indicates support for the ELS method of Clock",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        539.96,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0004",
      "text": "Synchronization.  If this bit is set to zero, the Nx_Port or Fabric does not support the ELS method of",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        69.65,
        540.02,
        80.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0005",
      "text": "Clock Synchronization.  If this bit is set to one, the Nx_Port or Fabric is capable of receiving CSU ELS",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        81.65,
        539.93,
        92.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0006",
      "text": "frames and acting upon them (see FC-FS-2).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        93.65,
        294.85,
        104.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0007",
      "text": "6.6.5.7  Receive Data_Field Size",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        118.97,
        245.94,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0008",
      "text": "The Receive Data_Field Size is a value (word 1, bits 11-0) that specifies the largest Data_Field Size",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        142.96,
        539.95,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0009",
      "text": "for a frame (see FC-FS-2) that may be received by the Nx_Port supplying the Service Parameters as",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        154.96,
        540.06,
        166.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0010",
      "text": "a Sequence Recipient.  Values less than 256 or greater than 2 112 are invalid.  Values shall be a",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        166.96,
        539.94,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0011",
      "text": "multiple of four bytes.  An Nx_Port shall support a Data Field size of at least 256 bytes.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        178.96,
        479.28,
        190.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0012",
      "text": "In Class 1 and 6 the Receive Data_Field size represents the largest Data_Field size that an Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        202.96,
        540.03,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0013",
      "text": "is able to receive after a dedicated connection is established.  The connect-request Data_Field size",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        214.96,
        539.93,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0014",
      "text": "is specified in the Buffer-to-Buffer Receive Data_Field size in Common Service Parameters (see",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        226.96,
        539.85,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0015",
      "text": "6.6.2.6).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        238.96,
        132.67,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0016",
      "text": "The Receive Data_Field size for Class 2, and Class 3 shall be equal to or less than the Buffer-to-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.96,
        540.15,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0017",
      "text": "Buffer Receive Data_Field size specified in the Common Service Parameters.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        274.96,
        439.2,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0018",
      "text": "6.6.5.8  Concurrent Sequences",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        298.96,
        241.49,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0019",
      "text": "Concurrent Sequences (word 2, bits 23-16) shall specify the number of Sequence Status Blocks",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        322.96,
        540.03,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0020",
      "text": "available in the Nx_Port supplying the Service Parameters for tracking the progress of a Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        334.96,
        539.81,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0021",
      "text": "as a Sequence Recipient.  The maximum number of Concurrent Sequences that may be specified is",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        346.96,
        539.99,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0022",
      "text": "255 per Nx_Port as a Recipient that may be allocated across all classes.  The total number of Con-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        358.96,
        540.02,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0023",
      "text": "current Recipient Sequences that may be open across all classes by a single Nx_Port is specified in",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.96,
        540.0,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0024",
      "text": "the Common Service Parameter field (see 6.6.2.7). Allowable values for this field is 01h - FFh. The",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        382.96,
        539.79,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0025",
      "text": "value 00 is reserved.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        394.96,
        188.19,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0026",
      "text": "NOTE 18 – The maximum number of open Sequences between two Nx_Ports is the sum of the Concurrent",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        419.18,
        539.91,
        429.22
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0027",
      "text": "Sequences fields reported in the PLOGI and LS_ACC of the PLOGI.",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        430.22,
        376.25,
        440.26
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0028",
      "text": "IN Class 1 and 6, the SEQ_ID values shall range from 0 to L, inclusively, where L is the value of the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.97,
        540.0,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0029",
      "text": "Concurrent Sequence field.  During a Class 1 Connection an Nx_Port shall support the maximum",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        466.97,
        539.96,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0030",
      "text": "number of Concurrent Sequences specified during Login.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.97,
        348.73,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0031",
      "text": "In Class 2 and 3, the SEQ_ID values shall range from 0 to 255.  In Class 2 an Nx_Port may respond",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        502.97,
        540.08,
        514.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0032",
      "text": "with a P_BSY to a frame initiating a new Sequence if Nx_Port resources are not available.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        514.97,
        493.71,
        526.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0033",
      "text": "6.6.5.9  end-to-end Credit",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        538.96,
        215.34,
        550.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0034",
      "text": "The Nx_Port End-to-end Credit field (word 2, bits 14-0) is the maximum number of Data frames that",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        540.09,
        574.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0035",
      "text": "may be transmitted by an Nx_Port without receipt of an accompanying ACK or Link_Response",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        539.96,
        586.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0036",
      "text": "frames.  The minimum value of the Nx_Port End-to-end Credit field is one.  The Nx_Port End-to-end",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        586.96,
        540.02,
        598.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0037",
      "text": "Credit field specified is associated with the number of buffers available for holding the Data_Field of a",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        598.96,
        539.99,
        610.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0038",
      "text": "frame and processing the contents of that Data_Field by the Nx_Port supplying the Service Parame-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        610.96,
        540.09,
        622.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0039",
      "text": "ters.  The Nx_Port End-to-end Credit field is not applicable to Class 3 since ACK frames are not",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        622.96,
        540.04,
        634.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0040",
      "text": "used.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        634.96,
        120.42,
        646.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0041",
      "text": "In order to ensure frame identification integrity, the Nx_Port end-to-end Credit field is defined as a 15-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        659.02,
        540.12,
        670.14
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0042",
      "text": "bit field while SEQ_CNT is a 16-bit field.  This ensures that end-to-end Credit never exceeds one-half",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        671.02,
        540.1,
        682.14
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p189_s0043",
      "text": "of the maximum SEQ_CNT.  Bit 15 shall be set to zero.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        683.02,
        340.33,
        694.14
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
  "asset_ids": []
}